	"title": "Les verbes en -er — Regular present tense",
	"objective": "Describe everyday actions using regular -er verbs (A1: can describe habits and routines in simple terms).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: one pattern for most verbs (and silent endings!)",
		"body": "About 90% of French verbs end in **-er** and share ONE set of endings: je parl**e**, tu parl**es**, il/elle parl**e**, nous parl**ons**, vous parl**ez**, ils/elles parl**ent**. ⚠️ The **-ent** ending is SILENT: *ils parlent* sounds exactly like *il parle*. Hindi verbs also change with the subject (मैं बोलता/बोलती हूँ), so the idea of agreement is familiar — just learn this one French pattern."
	},
